name: Appetite Classic

reviews.review_text:
Enjoy a breezy afternoon sipping on some beers or cocktails and Goan food on the first floor of this restaurant.

With the beautiful view of the town below, this probably is the selling point of this restaurant.

The food is good but the view is better.
Just spend a lazy afternoon here and enjoy your food.

We wanted to go for a rainy Sunday afternoon thali and had heard good things about this place. Unfortunately they don’t serve their thalis on Sunday.
We stayed for lunch anyway.

The service was quite relaxed in the typical Goan style, but it was worth the wait with the amazing prawn curry and prawn rava fry which were just outstanding and our favourites!

We also had silver fish fry, chinak fry -‘d surmai fry, along with some fish caldin.
These were all good, but not the best we’ve ever eaten.

What makes this place worth it is the prawn curry of course, but also the stunning views! It is in a gorgeous green location overlooking trees and was absolutely perfect in the monsoon!

They also have an AC section which would be great during the summers, but then you lose the views.

It’s a good option if you’re in mapusa and want a nice open space instead of being in a cramped restaurant.

The food was decent but the service was very slow . The waiter didn't even clear our plate once done with starters. We came through swiggy dine out and it was mentioned with free drink but the restaurant disagreed and caused a problem. The worst part was the serradura desert i had. It was just full of cream and only pinch of biscuit powder. It was very upsetting. Please improve on these points. Would love to change my reviews about it in the near future. Thank you.

description:
**Dining at Appetite Classic: A Taste of Goa with a View**

Nestled in the vibrant heart of Mapusa, Goa, Appetite Classic has charmed its way into the hearts of over 1,162 diners, earning a commendable rating of 3.8 stars. This bustling eatery is particularly favored for its seafood offerings, with notable mentions of fish dishes occurring 21 times among customer feedback. Many patrons come for dinner, finding respite in its relaxing ambiance and hearty quantities of food.

**Ambiance & Design**  
Stepping into Appetite Classic, you’re greeted with a breezy and relaxed vibe, perfect for leisure dining. The dining area is thoughtfully designed to maximize the stunning views of the lush greenery that surrounds the locale. Customers have shared images highlighting the restaurant’s high ceilings and open-air layout, allowing for natural sunlight to pour in, creating an inviting atmosphere. The first floor, in particular, is a favorite spot for enjoying cold beers or cocktails while gazing at the picturesque landscape, a sentiment strongly echoed in customer reviews.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**  
The menu at Appetite Classic is a delightful celebration of Goan cuisine, with seafood taking center stage. Signature dishes such as the prawn curry and prawn rava fry have garnered rave reviews, often deemed "amazing" by returning guests. One reviewer expressed how the prawn curry was the highlight of their meal, while other fish preparations such as the silver fish fry and surmai fry were also praised for their flavors.

Images shared by diners showcase beautifully plated dishes, which not only satisfy the palate but are also a feast for the eyes. However, it's noteworthy that while the food is generally regarded as good, some diners felt that certain dishes, like the serradura dessert, fell short in execution. Presentation is important, but some patrons have pointed out a disconnect between expectations and reality for some items.

**Customer Experience & Service**  
Customer experiences at Appetite Classic have been a mixed bag, particularly regarding service. While many have appreciated the friendly, laid-back Goan hospitality, others have reported slower service times, especially during peak hours. One review highlighted a situation where the staff missed clearing plates promptly, indicating areas for improvement. Despite these hiccups, guests seem willing to overlook service delays for the quality of food and ambience, with many expressing a desire to revisit.

For those heading in without reservations, understanding that it can get busy, especially for dinners, is essential. The restaurant does offer an air-conditioned section that provides relief from the heat but risks losing that breathtaking view.

**Popularity & Reviews**  
Appetite Classic has made a notable impact on social media, particularly among local Goans and tourists seeking a quintessential Goan dining experience. The lively atmosphere and scenic views keep diners coming back, and while some reviews point out inconsistencies in service and food execution, the fondness for the prawn curry seems to unite customers in their recommendations.

**Utilizing Visual Content**  
Diners have shared pictures that capture both the interior charm and the vibrantly presented dishes. For instance, the lush greenery visible through the open-air design stands out in the imagery and echoes the sentiments found in reviews about enjoying a meal in nature’s embrace. From glasses filled with colorful cocktails to steaming plates of prawn curry, the visual representations amplify the restaurant’s appeal.

In summary, Appetite Classic offers a commendable taste of Goa, with its standout seafood offerings and breathtaking views of the town below. While there are areas needing attention, such as service speed and food consistency, the overall dining experience remains delightful for those looking to indulge in good food against a magnificent landscape backdrop.
